body:

If you shave the zebra it would have no stripes.

author: TrueCryptoFan
body: Yeah it probably does...I think the vaccine plays are clear and well known...the next big issue is the distribution issue of the vaccines 💉 due to the intense cold 🥶 storage requirements. Betting on Zebra Tech you are in a way still betting on the vaccine...all companies use their tech already and the demand is about to increase

author: dvdmovie1
body:
> Walmart has 10,000+ locations that all can function as warehouses. That offers an advantage for delivery times.

Target's use of stores as fulfillment centers has been pretty exceptional. Look at results today: Same-day services (Order Pick Up, Drive Up and Shipt) +217%.  Walmart doing this quite well, too.

Zebra (ZBRA) also benefiting. 

"About 30% of Zebra’s business is retail, and it supplies all the major players. Management is careful not to talk about customers, but strolling through stores, investors can see Zebra devices in the hands of retail associates at Home Depot (HD), Walmart (WMT), and Target (TGT).

Amazon.com (AMZN) drivers in blue trucks also use Zebra technology. Amazon sales growth has averaged 39% year over year for the past two quarters. Sales are expected to top $118 billion in the fourth quarter—the first time quarterly sales will eclipse 12 figures." (https://www.barrons.com/articles/this-supplier-stock-is-soaring-because-amazon-is-crushing-it-51604421513)
